# LinkedIn Strategy Skills for Designers

Claude skills for building a real presence on LinkedIn — without sounding like everyone else.

Each skill is tailored to a specific design discipline. Instead of explaining your goals every session, the skill loads your strategy automatically so Claude can write posts, plan content, and give advice grounded in your actual work.

---

## Skills by designer type

| Designer type | Skill | Best for |
|---|---|---|
| Product designer · Lead designer · Founding designer · Design generalist | [`product-designer-linkedin-strategy`](./product-designer-linkedin-strategy/) | Designers who own the full product lifecycle across business, user, and technical dimensions |
| UI designer · Visual designer · Interface designer · Design system designer | [`ui-designer-linkedin`](./ui-designer-linkedin/) | Designers whose work is primarily visual interfaces |
| UX designer · UX researcher · Service designer · Interaction designer | [`ux-designer-linkedin`](./ux-designer-linkedin/) | Designers whose work is primarily research and user goals |
| Digital designer · Graphic designer · Marketing designer · Social media designer | [`digital-designer-linkedin`](./digital-designer-linkedin/) | Designers who produce commercial visual content for platforms |

> **UX/UI designer?** Start with `ui-designer-linkedin` if visuals are central to your work, or `ux-designer-linkedin` if you lean toward research and user goals.

