## What each skill covers

### [`product-designer-linkedin-strategy`](./product-designer-linkedin-strategy/)

Built for designers who own the full product lifecycle — from discovery through delivery and iteration. Product designers sit at the intersection of user needs, business viability, and technical constraints, and their LinkedIn content should reflect that. This skill teaches you to lead with decisions and outcomes, not just craft.

Covers: 7 content pillars (product decisions, business impact stories, cross-functional work, discovery, strategy takes, career stories, conversion), HPASS framework, humanized writing rules, profile optimization, goal-specific guidance for job seekers and consultants.

### [`ui-designer-linkedin`](./ui-designer-linkedin/)

Built around the one advantage UI designers underuse: their work is already visual. A great screenshot with three lines of context often beats 300 words.

Covers: 7 content pillars specific to visual design (component breakdowns, interface teardowns, Figma workflows, visual trend takes), writing rules that keep posts from sounding AI-generated, post types for authority and conversion.

### [`ux-designer-linkedin`](./ux-designer-linkedin/)

Built for designers whose best work is invisible — research findings, usability sessions, journey maps, and the moments where advocacy changed a product decision. UX designers have to make invisible things visible through words. This skill is built around that.

Covers: 7 content pillars (research insights, usability findings, methodology reveals, user advocacy moments, stakeholder work, field takes, conversion), writing rules that keep posts grounded and human, profile optimization that shows process not just polish.

### [`digital-designer-linkedin`](./digital-designer-linkedin/)

For designers who produce commercial visual content for digital platforms — social media graphics, web banners, email templates, display ads, campaign assets. Their output is already formatted for screens, which is exactly where LinkedIn lives.

Covers: 7 content pillars (campaign breakdowns with metrics, before/after iteration, platform-specific design, client brief work, tools and workflow, visual trend takes, conversion), formatting rules, and writing guidance that sounds like someone who does client work every day.

### [`humanize-writing`](./HUMANIZE.md)

A writing editor that makes any text sound like a real person wrote it. Catches the patterns that give away AI-written content — parallel negation, tricolons, dramatic reveals, mirror sentences, inflation language — and rewrites them into something a human would actually say.

Use this standalone or alongside the LinkedIn skills.

