## How to install

### Option 1 — Cowork (drag and drop)
Download the skill folder and drag the `.skill` file into Claude's Cowork interface.

### Option 2 — Claude Code (copy to skills directory)

```bash
cp -r designer-linkedin-strategy ~/.claude/skills/
```

Reload Claude Code. The skill appears in your available skills list automatically.

### Option 3 — Paste as system prompt
Each skill is a plain markdown file. Paste the contents of `SKILL.md` directly into a Claude project's custom instructions if you prefer not to use the skills system.

---

## How it works

Skills load into Claude's context when you start a task that matches their description. You don't have to name the skill — Claude picks it up based on what you're asking for.

Examples:
- "Write me a LinkedIn post about my design system work" → triggers `ui-designer-linkedin`
- "Give me 5 post ideas for this week" → triggers the relevant strategy skill
- "This post sounds too AI, can you fix it?" → triggers `humanize-writing`

Each skill folder:

```
skill-name/
├── SKILL.md         — the main instructions Claude reads
└── references/      — supporting files loaded on demand
```

